Illegible.definition: Not clear enough to be read, hard or impossible to read because it is badly written or printed

Imbecile.definition: Informal-a stupid person, a person with abnormally low intelligence, a fool

Immaculate.definition: Completely clean or tidy, free from flaws or mistakes

Improvise.definition: To compose and perform without preparation, make from whatever is available

Impudent.definition: Not showing proper respect, shamelessly bold
